(93, 7, 'facebook', '144884762309778_375843235880595', 'e623a3071556d6c57ef2cc572bd2b75e', 'The #incredibleindia photography campaign is on!!!.While there are prizes to be won, the sheer experience of contributing to this campaign will be huge! A huge, HUGE collection of wonderful photographs that depict our country is being built through this campaign!\n\nThe details of participating in this campaign are here: http://googleindia.blogspot.in/2013/09/experience-incredibleindia-with-google.html\n\nthose interested are requested to go to the above link and follow the instructions given therein.\n\nMoreover, The Google Student Club,Jorhat Engineering College in association with FotoKraft is pleased to announce that a photography competition is being organized in parallel..\nAll that will be needed is a G+ account where the photographs have to be uploaded with the unique feature of G+ #tag\nHere are the guidelines for uploading Photographs in G+ account..\n1. Add the hashtag #GSA_jec_jrt for the competition to be held among college students and use #incredibleindia for Incredible India campaign, It will help us in getting your photographs directly from Photographer''s account\n2. The last date of the competition organised by GSC is November 7â€¦\n3.The 20 pictures that will get the maximum +1s will be shortlistedâ€¦ So, be sure to garner support and likes for your pictures.\n4. The shortlisted pictures will be judged by competent people.\n\nThe rules for the photography competition organized by GSC and Fotokraft are-\n1.The photograph must be clicked by the photographer himself.\n2.No manipulation which can change the meaning of the photograph is allowed\n3.No watermark is allowed.\n4.There is no hard and fast rule for dimensions.The photographs can be panorama,photosphere etc.\n\nN.B.:There is no specific theme.Anyone can participate in the competition.For example: Our College JEC, Places: Jorhat or One''s native village,city, Heritage and Natural beauty of Assam, any place of India or any Kind of travel photograph is allowed in the competition.\n\nFor more information do contact -\nJaydeep Deka(Creative Lead of GSC)-9864820901\nPartha Pratim Barman (Event Manager of GSC)-9613475247\nAashish Das(Event Manager of GSC)-9613745467\nSrishti Dasgupta(Google Student Ambassador)-7896006069\nPulak Basumatary(Executive Member,FotoKraft)-9706211842\n\nFor more details and updates, please follow the g+ page---https://plus.google.com/u/0/b/107642864329076896388/107642864329076896388/about', 'EN', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/144884762309778_375843235880595', 'link', NULL, 'http://external.ak.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQDk9pFjPQiWRGpP&w=154&h=154&url=http%3A%2F%2F3.bp.blogspot.com%2F-6m4fLICDSiM%2FUicu5PEalyI%2FAAAAAAAAAVI%2FArtqhL6TBLA%2Fs640%2Fimage.png', 'http://googleindia.blogspot.in/2013/09/experience-incredibleindia-with-google.html', 'Official Google India Blog: Experience #IncredibleIndia with Google+ Photos', 'googleindia.blogspot.com', NULL, 'Travel/leisure', NULL, 'FotoKraft', NULL, '144884762309778', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, NULL, 'new', '2013-09-23T08:43:15+0000', '1379925795', '2013-09-24 11:34:01', '2013-09-24 21:34:01'),
